Python(file_path="./data_analysis.py"):
```python
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load the data
data = pd.read_csv("restaurants.csv")

# Calculate the percentage of restaurants offering online ordering options
online_orders = data[data["online_ordering"] == "Yes"]["rating"].value_counts(normalize=True)

# Calculate the percentage of restaurants not offering online ordering options
no_online_orders = data[data["online_ordering"] == "No"]["rating"].value_counts(normalize=True)

# Combine the results
result = pd.concat([online_orders, no_online_orders], axis=1, keys=["Online Orders", "No Online Orders"])

# Create a stacked bar chart
ax = result.plot(kind="bar", stacked=True, figsize=(10, 6))
ax.set_title("Percentage of Restaurants' Online Order Option by Rating")
ax.set_xlabel("Rating")
ax.set_ylabel("Percentage of Online Orders")

# Save the chart as 'result.jpg'
plt.savefig("result.jpg")
```
